```javascript
// script.js
document.getElementById("show-modal").addEventListener("click", () => {
    const chatHistoryModal = document.getElementById("chat-history-modal");
    chatHistoryModal.style.display = "block";

    const chatHistory = [
        { user: "Human", text: "Message 1" },
        { user: "Bot", text: "Message 2" },
        { user: "Human", text: "Message 3" },
        { user: "Bot", text: "Message 4" },
    ];

    chatHistoryModal.innerHTML = "";

    chatHistory.forEach((message, index) => {
        const messageElement = document.createElement("div");
        const messageText = document.createElement("div");

        if (message.user === "Human") {
            messageElement.classList.add("user");
        } else {
            messageElement.classList.add("bot");
        }
        messageText.classList.add("message-text");
        messageText.textContent = message.text;

        messageElement.appendChild(messageText);
        chatHistoryModal.appendChild(messageElement);
    });
});
```
This code will create a simple fake chatbot using an HTML modal. The Bot's messages will be displayed in the first two messages in the modal, while the human's messages will be displayed in the last two messages. When the user clicks the "Show Modal" button, the chat history will be displayed in the modal.

